      <td>In a similar way in which [[Gaze stabilization is preprocessing in vision</td>
      <td>gaze movements stabilize the orientation of the image being projected onto the retina]], the pupil light response stabilizes the brightness of the image. The pupil light response is merely tasked with acting as a buffer, maintaining isoluminance for a short period, while the eye-level chemical adaptations kick in.</td>
